                                            <p class="kicker">Shielded No Longer: Top EU Court Invalidates Privacy Shield Framework and Clarifies Use of Standard Contractual Clauses as Bases for EU-U.S. Data Transfers</p>
                                            <p class="post"><div><p>Shielded No Longer: Top EU Court Invalidates Privacy Shield Framework and Clarifies Use of Standard Contractual Clauses as Bases for EU-U.S. Data Transfers -

Yesterday, the Court of Justice of the European Union (CJEU) issued its long-awaited opinion in Data Protection Commissioner v. Facebook Ireland and Maximillian Schrems (Schrems II), a landmark case challenging the continued legitimacy of Standard Contractual Clauses agreements as a basis for transferring the personal data of EU residents to the United States... (<a href="http://vlex.com/vid/shielded-no-longer-top-846516828" target="_blank">See Article</a>)</p></div></p>
                                            <p class="date">Jul 20, 2020 6:33 AM</p>
