                                        <li>
                                            <p class="kicker">European Court of Justice Strikes Down Privacy Shield</p>
                                            <p class="post"><div><p>The European Court of Justice (ECJ) struck down the Privacy Shield – the legal mechanism that allowed many small and medium sized companies to transfer personal data from the European Union to the United States without violating the European Union’s General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). This is the second time in five years that the… (<a href="http://vlex.com/vid/european-court-of-justice-846460615" target="_blank">See Article</a>)</p></div></p>
                                            <p class="date">Jul 17, 2020 6:33 AM</p>
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
